Bluetongue [BTV], Italy
-----------------------
Information received on [and dated] 8 Sep 2016 from Prof Dr Romano Marabelli, Chief Veterinary Officer, Secretary General, Ministry of Health, Rome, Italy

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 30 Aug 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 1 Sep 2016
Reason for notification: new strain of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (8)
Outbreak 1 (BTV4_1): Belluno, Alano di Piave, Veneto
Date of start of the outbreak: 30 Aug 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 500 / 3 / - / - / -
Affected population: The positivity regards 3 ewes belonging to a group of animals on pasture.

